Combine 5 cups @water{5%cups}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2}, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} in a #medium pot{}. Bring to a boil. Once boiling, reduce heat to low. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @Arborio Rice{3/4%cup} and @Butter{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until rice is translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reduce heat to medium.

Add stock, ½ cup at a time, stirring after each addition. Allow rice to absorb most of the liquid before adding more. Continue until rice is al dente and creamy, about ~{30%minutes}.

While risotto cooks, wash and dry all produce. Trim and discard bottom 2 inches from @Asparagus{6%oz}. Cut off asparagus tips, then cut stalks on an angle into bite-sized pieces (about 1 inch long). Dice @Roma Tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

When risotto has cooked about 25 minutes, add tomato and asparagus to pan. Cook, stirring, until veggies have softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tbsp} and half the @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup} into risotto. Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Divide risotto between plates and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Garnish with @?Chili Flakes{1%tsp} if desired.